    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Free Peoples: <br />
Bid 0, if you win bid go second. Playing your sites is huge. If you got nice setup, Gandalf and some weapons make 1-3, if not stop at 2. Collect Dwarven Skills usually using it&#39;s TOIL 2 once to play it for 1, they are the key in late game. Against Castamir or Witch with his toys just use Terrible and Evil, it is also very useful against Enquea, ToTO or against Wormtongue. After quick setup with Trollshaw / Barazinbar you choke twilight and got high strength companions. Remember to fetch Blood Runs or Sharp Defense with Guile if needed, and remember to use Fury if needed cuz u got 2 in deck. Against most shadows u can easily go to 9. THe only problem can be Burden Hordes, but choknig twilight + keeping some event(s) will let you survive till drawing Glamdring. <br />
<br />
Shadow: <br />
Try to get Castamir+Halberd at site 2 (if they got good setup like Eomer+toys or Durin + toys) use Moria Stairway. Against Dwarfs collect tokens on Ships to return Sails after BRC. Basicly Castamir + Halberd is killing one or two companions. fter killing some comps and collecting Sails jsut use it and kill. Halaberd is used to make Castamir strength +2 from Enduring keyword and to produce twilight for Red Wrath. Bold Man can be a gamebreaker, killing some poor companion with Castamir and then discarding Durin III / Eomer / Sam, GEW or other killing machine. Quelled gets rid of nasty Sword-racks / Arrow-Slits or Don&#39;t look at Them. <br />
<br />
Deck is very solid, I finished with it March Online PSQ with a result of 6-0. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
